Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getCPFUserAttributes(25.10)                        getCPFUserAttributes(25.10)

Name
       getCPFUserAttributes  - Reports the user_attributes of the power domain
       or net specified in the CPF file

Syntax
       getCPFUserAttributes

       [-help]

       -domain <domainName> | -net <netName>

       Reports the user_attributes of the power domain or net specified in the
       CPF file. If the domain or net has no user_attributes in the CPF  file,
       then this command reports an empty string.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each getCPFUserAttributes parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getCPFUserAttribute.

       -domain
              Specifies  the  name of the power domain containing the user_at-
              tributes.

       -net   Specifies the name of the net having the user_attributes.

Related Information
              * For more information, see the  following  topics  in  the  Low
                Power Design chapter of the User Guide.

                * "Overview"

                * "Power Domain Shutdown and Scaling"

                * "Support for the Common Power Format"

